The paper deals with maintaining conflict-free colorings of geometric objects in the plane under insertions and deletions, which is a problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) as it presents algorithms and methods for maintaining conflict-free colorings efficiently. Finally, the paper involves graph theory (cs.GT) as it deals with coloring problems.
